<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870908-0132 </DOCNO><HL> Letters to the Editor:Light Up Our Lives</HL><DD> 09/08/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> UTILITIES (UTI) </IN><TEXT>   It was encouraging to read your July 8 story about social worker Paula Ross of New York State Electric andamp; Gas Corp. and her efforts to help impoverished customers find public assistance to help pay their bills. Aside from illuminating Ms. Ross's demonstrated competence and dedication, the story shows how businesses, acting in their own best interests, can lend a helping hand to individuals and contribute to the community which, in turn, makes these businesses viable.    Rae Mark Hamilton   Director, Office of Public Information    National Association of Social Workers   Silver Spring, Md.</TEXT></DOC>